268. Exsilium . . . habuere .· the long life of 0. Marius was attend- ed with innumerable miseries. Being conquered by Sylla, he fled to the marshes osMinturnoe, a town of old Latium, where he was taken and thrown into prison : but, escaping thence into Africa, he was oblig- ed to beg his bread through the streets of Carthago. He afterwards returned to Rome, on the departure of Sylla to the Mithridatio war, and becoming consul, then for the seventh time, died in a few months, having amply revenged himself upon his enemies.
